<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10435] Index selectivity calculation is incorrect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10435</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;SecondaryIndexManager::getBestIndexFor&lt;/tt&gt;, the calculation to choose the most selective from a set of candidate indexes is incorrect. It currently chooses the index which returns the highest value from &lt;tt&gt;Index::getEstimatedResultRows&lt;/tt&gt;. Obviously it should return the one with the fewest estimated results.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
